<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="409" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-24"><hi rend="italic">June 24, 1895</hi></date>.
                                (Received July 6.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 378.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report, in reply to
                            your No. 338, of the 5th instant, touching the <hi rend="italic">Alliança</hi> incident, that I have duly communicated your
                            acceptance of the explanation made by the minister of state, as nearly
                            as possible in your own language.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hannis Taylor.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>